-- U.S., Colombia Reach Agreement on Free-Trade Labor Accord
-- B y   R o g e r   R u n n i n g e n
-- 2012-04-15T17:30:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-15/u-s-colombia-reach-agreement-on-free-trade-labor-accord.html
The U.S. and Colombia have reached
agreement on a free trade agreement that includes protection of
labor unions, U.S. Trade Representative  Ron Kirk  said.  The agreement provides “an opportunity to help stand up
for the rights of workers” worldwide, Kirk told reporters at a
Latin American summit meeting in Cartagena, Colombia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Roger Runningen in Washington at 
